01:05:07,480 --> 01:05:14,320
the strategy that YouTube used to grow, but it was 
two years before YouTube introduced the approach.

727
01:05:14,320 --> 01:05:19,800
It feels like you basically created Zynga, is what 
I'm hearing there. So let's move further down the  

728
01:05:19,800 --> 01:05:25,040
funnel. So we've talked about activation, 
onboarding. The next phase that you focus  

729
01:05:25,040 --> 01:05:30,000
on is basically some people call this growth 
loops, growth engines, flywheels. Basically  

730
01:05:30,000 --> 01:05:34,920
it's the thing that helps your business grow 
and something I am curious if this resonates. 

731
01:05:34,920 --> 01:05:41,720
I found there's basically four ways to grow and 
usually one of these engines is responsible for  

732
01:05:41,720 --> 01:05:45,600
almost all of your growth. So what I've seen 
is basically you're going to go through sales,  

733
01:05:45,600 --> 01:05:48,920
you're going to grow through SEO, 
you're going to go through virality,  

734
01:05:48,920 --> 01:05:53,600
word of mouth or paid growth. Does 
that resonate? Does that feel right?

735
01:05:53,600 --> 01:05:59,560
And I wouldn't say it's necessarily one 
or the other. I think Bounce is a really  

736
01:05:59,560 --> 01:06:09,760
interesting example where SEO is super important 
for Bounce. So people who are essentially saying,  

737
01:06:09,760 --> 01:06:14,480
"Luggage storage, Paris. Luggage storage..." 
Most people when they're trying to find a place  

738
01:06:14,480 --> 01:06:20,080
to store their luggage, they're starting with 
